The only difference between an H1B hire and an illegal alien hire is that instead of stealing an extreme low wage manual labor job, they are stealing a higher paying job from middle income Americans. (and have the same wage depressing effect as well)

These companies are, in effect, selling access to America in exchange for low wages and circumventing the immigration process. 

The US military trains people to work on the most advanced fighter jets in the world with a few weeks to a few months training.  

There is ZERO excuse for these large companies to be allowed to sell access to America just because they make larger donations to politicians than individuals can.

If it is about a specialized job, FORCE THE COMPANY to have a SHORT TERM H1B, for a specific role, and only if they have demonstrated a TRAINING PROGRAM where the need for that H1B will be fixed in short order.

As a worker for a big tech company, there is NO part of my job I cannot train someone to do OJT in just a few months.
